<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT> B2BInfoReader - read and analyze the locally stored b2b.info log and call registerEror on &#34;stream 1&#34; messages </COMMENT>
</SEQUENCE>

<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT>                         &#34;stream 1&#34; messages are the messages that are determined to be suitable for USD ticket creation </COMMENT>
</SEQUENCE>

<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT></COMMENT>
</SEQUENCE>

<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT>   This service is run on the IS scheduler on a set interval.  It reads the *local* b2b.info log file and therefore must be scheduled </COMMENT>
</SEQUENCE>

<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT>   to run on *each* instance of a cluster.  The service maintains a config file, B2BInfoReader-priorrun.xml, stored in the local pipeline folder, to keep </COMMENT>
</SEQUENCE>

<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT>   track of the position within the b2b.info file where the service has previously processed the ever-growing b2b.info file. </COMMENT>
</SEQUENCE>

<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT></COMMENT>
</SEQUENCE>

<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT>   Note that the fully qualified /webMethods10/b2b.info filename is supplied as an input parameter to this service. </COMMENT>
</SEQUENCE>

<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT>   Note also that this service is transitional, such that when error messages are no longer recorded using mesozoic-age technology, this service can be removed. </COMMENT>
</SEQUENCE>

<SEQUENCE TIMEOUT="" EXIT-ON="FAILURE">
  <COMMENT></COMMENT>
